Describe- Why did Steve Ballmer call the GPL a virus?
The license continues itself by requiring all derivatives also use the license, therefore becoming similar to a virus.

What is the relationship / difference between open source and proprietary software?
Open source software gives you the source code to the software, but proprietary software only gives you certain rights to the software.

What are the differences between the GPL and the MIT license? 
With the GPL license, you have to license all derivative works under the same license.
With the MIT license, all you have to do is reproduce the license and copyright notice.
You do not have to license the derivative with the MIT license.
